events.body:
@hebasto Thanks for the review. I've updated the action to use the built-in `GITHUB_WORKSPACE` and removed the redundant variable. 

Regarding the injection hardening: while these contexts aren't directly user-controlled here, mapping them to environment variables is a more robust way to handle multiline inputs and prevents potential quote-mangling in the `bash -c` wrapping. 

@real-or-random Thanks for the ACK. Glad to see support for establishing safer patterns in the CI scripts.
